s/Cursed_goblin_hammer.png?d2f85\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"20\" height=\"27\" data-file-width=\"20\" data-file-height=\"27\" />  Goblin Invasion</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/2013_Goblin_Invasion\" title=\"2013 Goblin Invasion\">2013</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/2014_Goblin_Invasion\" title=\"2014 Goblin Invasion\">2014</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\"><img alt=\"20th anniversary cape.png\" src=\"/images/20th_anniversary_cape.png?3e370\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"31\" height=\"31\" data-file-width=\"31\" data-file-height=\"31\" /> Other events</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/2013_Rare_Drops\" title=\"2013 Rare Drops\">2013 Rare Drops</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Big_Cats_%26_WWF\" title=\"Big Cats &amp; WWF\">Big Cats &amp; WWF</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/World_666_event\" title=\"World 666 event\">World 666 event</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Gilbert's Colours</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Mobile_Anniversary\" title=\"Mobile Anniversary\">Mobile Anniversary</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/20th_Anniversary_event\" title=\"20th Anniversary event\">20th Anniversary event</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mediawiki‚Äê7bfb498f95‚Äêlgkzc\nCached time: 20220516151112\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\n[SMW] In‚Äêtext annotation parser time: 0 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.132 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.194 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 799/1000000\nPost‚Äêexpand include size: 26037/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 3250/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‚Äêexpand size: 1809/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.021/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1076863/367001600 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  110.186      1 -total\n 27.85%   30.692      1 Template:Gilbert's_Colours\n 25.73%   28.355      1 Template:CiteTwitter\n 15.37%   16.940      2 Template:Navbox\n 14.36%   15.824      2 Template:CiteGeneral\n 11.21%   12.350      2 Template:Ctg\n  8.07%    8.897      1 Template:Events\n  7.12%    7.844      1 Template:Infobox_Event\n  5.65%    6.224      1 Template:Reflist\n  5.60%    6.170      1 Template:WP\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:99914-0!canonical and timestamp 20220516151111 and revision id 14272827. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{Infobox Event\n|name = Gilbert's Colours\n|image = [[File:Gilbert's Colours.png|300px]]\n|release = [[8 June]] [[2017]]\n|update = Pest Control & Open Weekend\n|removal = [[22 June]] [[2017]]\n|removalupdate = Mining Guild Expansion\n|reward = [[Rainbow scarf]]\n}}\n[[File:Rainbow.png|left|120px|One of the rainbows a player may find while searching for [[Rainbow strand]]s.]]\n'''Gilbert's Colours''' was an event that took place in ''[[Old School RuneScape]]'' as a promotion of {{WP|LGBT}} inclusivity.\n\nPlayers started the event by speaking to [[Gilbert]], a leprechaun found in the [[Lumbridge Castle]] courtyard. Gilbert asked the player to gather six [[Rainbow strand|strands of colours]] from rainbows found throughout Gielinor. Each colour represents a specific meaning based on the {{wp|Rainbow flag (LGBT movement)|rainbow flag}} in real-life.\n\nOnce the player gave Gilbert all six strands, he rewarded players with the [[rainbow scarf]].\n{{clear|left}}\n\n==Locations==\nEach of the clues refers to the meaning of one of the stripes on the rainbow flag.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable lighttable\"\n! colspan=\"2\" |Colour\n!Riddle\n!Location\n!Colour meaning\n|-\n|{{plinkt|Red rainbow strand|txt=Red}}\n|''\"South of my magical location, I see life! New adventurers and baldness rife.\"''\n|South of the [[Wizards' Tower]].\n|Life\n|-\n|{{plinkt|Orange rainbow strand|txt=Orange}}\n|''\"Beside me now, a person of healing. Those who test their luck, find this place appealing.\"''\n|East of the [[Duel Arena]] bank.\n|Healing\n|-\n|{{plinkt|Yellow rainbow strand|txt=Yellow}}\n|''\"On my face; shining sunlight. South of a dwarf whom redberries delight.\"''\n|The southern point of [[Mudskipper Point]].\n|Sunlight\n|-\n|{{plinkt|Green rainbow strand|txt=Green}}\n|''\"Lush natures and trees are to the east. The Green strand... no orange! No, blue! No, red! Green! Argh! There's so much bickering in this area it's hard to pinpoint its location...\"''\n|The entrance of the [[Goblin Village]].\n|Nature\n|-\n|{{plinkt|Blue rainbow strand|txt=Blue}}\n|''\"In this area, there's a silent and artistic harmony... Ironically, north-west, wizards kill newcomers effortlessly.\"''\n|In the [[ram]]s' pen, south of [[Varrock]].\n|Serenity\n|-\n|{{plinkt|Purple rainbow strand|txt=Purple}}\n|''\"The knights in this area, are full of Saradomin's spirit. On the top of this fortress, when I yell - all hear it!\"''\n|On the top floor of the [[White Knights' Castle]], just upstairs of [[Sir Amik Varze]].\n|Spirit\n|}\n\n==Controversy==\nGilbert's Colours was an extremely controversial event which received mixed opinions from the ''Old School RuneScape'' community. Criticism from dissenting players claimed it was too overtly political and thus out of place and \"irrelevant\" to the world of ''Old School RuneScape''.{{CiteGeneral|url=https://www.mic.com/articles/179183/old-school-runescape-players-rage-against-political-in-game-lgbtq-pride-event|title='Old School RuneScape' players rage against \"political\" in-game LGBTQ pride event|date=6 June 2017|accessdate=2022-02-19}} Upon announcement of the event on [[Mod Wolf]]'s personal Twitter account,{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Wolf|url=https://twitter.com/Jay_Wilton/status/871773754497650688|date=5 June 2017|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/neNqD|archivedate=9 April 2022}} it received significant backlash, culminating in offensive and inflammatory in-game protests (dubbed \"riots\") against the event which received outside media coverage.{{CiteGeneral|url=https://medium.com/@slimelia/how-a-pixelated-rainbow-spurred-a-virtual-riot-in-runescape-bd7193ee01d|title=How a Pixelated Rainbow Spurred a Virtual Riot in¬†RuneScape|date=8 June 2017|accessdate=2022-02-19|archiveurl=https://archive.is/joJJZ|archivedate=20 February 2022}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Gilbert's Colours}}\n{{Events}}\n[[Category:Jagex controversies]]"}